State of North Carolina
v.
Maurice Parker No. 136P16 Supreme Court of North Carolina. June 9, 2016 Robert C. Montgomery, Special Deputy Attorney General, William R. West, District Attorney, For State. Maurice Parker, Pro Per.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 13th of April 2016 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the Superior Court, Cumberland County, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court of that County:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 9th of June 2016."
